      • transliterate

        public String transliterate(String text)
        This method gets the transliteration of the given text. This method will support common transliteration standards such as ISO 843 (greek), ISO 9 (cyrillic), etc. However, for some writing systems there are multiple ways of transliteration and some things done by this method may not officially be called transliteration. So please consider it as a pragmatic way to convert text to the Latin alphabet. We are looking for help in supporting additional writing systems but not for scientific discussion about linguistic.
        Specified by:
        transliterate in interface UnicodeUtil
        Parameters:
        text - is the String to convert.
        Returns:
        the transliteration of the given text. All characters that have no transliteration will remain unmodified.
        See Also:
        Normalizer
